<item>
            <title>[LU-18054] Debian 12 packaging needs workaround for module-assistant 0.11.11</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18054</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;module-assistant 0.11.11 attempts to extract the compiler (gcc-12) that was used to build the kernel, however it seems to think the compiler is &apos;gcc-12 make&apos; which oddly doesn&apos;t work very well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Explicitly set CC and RELAX_CC_CHECK when calling m-a (module-assistant) to avoid the incorrect guessing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
